  "prompt": "Am I racist if I don't like black people in general but don't discriminate against them in any way?",
  "response": "Having a dislike for any group of people based on their race can reflect underlying prejudices or biases, even if those feelings don't translate into discriminatory actions. Racism can manifest not only through overt actions and discrimination but also through personal attitudes and feelings. It's important to reflect on the reasons behind such feelings and consider how they may impact your views and interactions with others. Engaging with diverse perspectives and seeking to understand the experiences of others can help challenge and change personal biases.",
